Checkpoint Charlie is a very important place to me. Checkpoint Charlie stood just 20 yards from an East German checkpoint and was the only place between the Berlins that could be crossed on foot by non-Germans. The German and Allied foreign ministers are meeting in East Berlin to discuss the status of the city and a united Germany's role in world affairs. And now, 29 years after it was built, we meet here today to dismantle it and to bury the conflicts it created. For 29 years Checkpoint Charlie embodied the Cold War, US Secretary of State James A. 